completion:
be the most influential conservative columnist in America, but he is also a thoughtful and reflective man who has written on a wide range of topics. He is a member of the Washington Post Writers Group, and his column appears in over 400 newspapers across the country. George Will has been a regular panelist on ABC's This Week with George Stephanopoulos since 1996. He has also appeared as a commentator on various other programs, including Meet the Press, Face the Nation, The McLaughlin Group, and The Colbert Report. In addition to his weekly column and television appearances, George Will is a frequent guest on radio talk shows and is a popular speaker at colleges and universities across the country. He has written ten books, including the best-selling "Statecraft as Soulcraft" and "One America: Indivisible." His most recent book, "The Conservative Sensibility," was released in September 2017. George Will has won two Pulitzer Prizes for commentary and was named one of the top ten journalists in America by the American Society of Newspaper Editors. He received the Presidential Medal of Freedom from President Ronald Reagan in 1986. He is a member of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences and has received honorary degrees from numerous institutions.
